column997: C&P is tackling the security issue (CVE-2024-3596) in redhat-RHEL7 package version 1.15.1-50.el7, which is a vulnerability in the RADIUS (Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service) protocol allows attackers to forge authentication responses when the Message-Authenticator attribute is not enforced. This issue arises from a cryptographically insecure integrity check using MD5, enabling attackers to spoof UDP-based RADIUS response packets. Our plan is to upgrade to krb5-libs version 1.15.1-55.el7_9.3, then test ensure the updates address the vulnerability. Also the Tenant Management 2 (TM2) C&P DevOps team is monitoring for any suspicious activity. Initial milestones: (30 days) - Meet with TM2 Development team to determine validity of finding. (60 days) - Create a plan to upgrade to krb5-libs version 1.15.1-55.el7_9.3. (90 days) - Deployment of updates to production environment.

column997: C&P is working the security issue (CVE-2022-2526) in systemd, this issue occurs due to the on_stream_io() function and dns_stream_complete() function in 'resolved-dns-stream.c' not incrementing the reference counting for the DnsStream object. Therefore, other functions and callbacks called can dereference the DNSStream object, causing the use-after-free when the reference is still used later. Initial milestones: (30 days) - Meet with TM2 Development team to determine validity of finding. (60 days) - Create a plan to update the affected systemd packages. (90 days) - Deployment of updates to production environment.

column997: C&P is working the security issue (CVE-2022-2526) in systemd, this issue occurs due to the on_stream_io() function and dns_stream_complete() function in 'resolved-dns-stream.c' not incrementing the reference counting for the DnsStream object. Therefore, other functions and callbacks called can dereference the DNSStream object, causing the use-after-free when the reference is still used later. Initial milestones: (30 days) - Meet with TM2 Development team to determine validity of finding. (60 days) - Create a plan to update the affected systemd packages. (90 days) - Deployment of updates to production environment.

column997: C&P is working the security issue (CVE-2022-25236) in Expat on Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7, which allows arbitrary code execution depending on how unexpected cases are handled inside the XML processor. Our plan is to restrict applications using the Expat library from processing untrusted XML content and update the affected Expat packages as soon as possible, then test ensure code changes address the vulnerability. Initial milestones: (30 days) - Meet with TM2 Development team to determine validity of finding. (60 days) - Create a plan to update the affected Expat packages. (90 days) - Deployment of updates to production environment.

For the Benefits Integration Platform (BIP) to maintain the VA Authority-to-Operate (ATO), DMDT hosted in the VAEC AWS environment must maintain certain application-focused security assessment requirements.

*Acceptance Criteria*: The attached security issue tasks are required to be renewed and maintained on an annual basis in order for DMDT to maintain the VA authority to operate (ATO).

column1: Capability to Complete Tenant Security Assessment (TSA) under the BIP ATO for Dynamic Medical Data Transformer (DMDT)
column35:
{*}Summary{*}: Benefits Integration Platform (BIP) provides a Platform as a Service environment (PaaS) in VA Enterprise Cloud (VAEC) AWS in which VA benefits, appeals, and memorials (BAM) applications are hosted. For the Benefits Integration Platform (BIP) to maintain the VA Authority-to-Operate (ATO), the BIP Tenant hosted in the VAEC AWS environment must initially meet and maintain certain application-focused assessment requirements.

For Dynamic Medical Data Transformer (DMDT) to be deployed on the BIP in a production environment, it must attain an "approved" Minor Application Security Assessment.

{*}Required Deliverables from Development Teams{*}: 
Sub-Task: Draft Documentation
Sub-Task: Provide Scans

*Other Sub-Tasks*
Sub-Task: Product Owner Review - POC is IA
Sub-Task: Submit VASI Entry - POC is C&P Tech Manager

*Benefit Statement:* By completing the VA Minor Application Security Assessment and obtaining a Minor Assessment ATO, (M.A.-ATO), Dynamic Medical Data Transformer (DMDT) can be deployed to the BIP production environment.

*Product Owners:* 
 * Christina Lawyer
